OK, maybe i don’t understand the version number here. is it for the definition or the package?

i thought it is the latter. if so, it should be a clear placeholder (e.g. “x.x”), or automatically filled in.

automatically filling it (and the homepage) could be done via

``` ts
const { latest, homepage } = await fetch(`https://registry.npmjs.org/${newPackageName}`)
    .then(r => r.json())
    .then((package) => {
        const { latest } = package['dist-tags']
        const { homepage } = package.versions[latest]
        return { latest, homepage }
    }).catch((e) => ({
        latest: 'x.x',
        homepage: 'Project: https://github.com/baz/foo (Does not have to be to GitHub, but prefer linking to a source code repository rather than to a project website.)',
    }))
```

